10 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
11 An Act relating to emergency medical services;
amending 63 O.S. 2021, Section 1-2502, which relates
12 to legislative findings and declarations; declaring
emergency medical services to be considered essential
13 services for certain purpose; and declaring an
emergency.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 63 O.S. 2021, Section 1-2502, is
18 amended to read as follows:
19 Section 1-2502. The Legislature hereby finds and declares that:
20 1. There is a critical shortage of providers of emergency care
21 for:
22 a. the delivery of fast, efficient emergency medical care
23 for the sick and injured at the scene of a medical
24
Req. No. 17433 Page 1

1 emergency and during transport to a health care
2 facility, and
3 b. the delivery of stabilizing and definitive care at a
4 health care facility; and
5 2. Improved emergency service is required to reduce the
6 mortality rate during the first critical minutes immediately
7 following the onset of a medical emergency; and
8 3. Solely for purposes of eligibility for federal funding,
9 emergency medical services licensed by the State shall be considered
10 essential services.
11 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
12 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
13 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
14 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
